<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 16:00 GMT, July 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Five Swiss nationals were held
hostage Wednesday when an armed man hijacked their small yacht off
the seaside town of Tolo near Nafplion in Greece's southwestern
Peleponnese peninsula. (Greece-Switzerland-Hostage)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CANBERRA -- Fiji coup leader George Speight, who took the prime
minister hostage in May, was arrested on Wednesday, Fijian media
reported. (Fiji-Speight-Arrest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French President Jacques Chirac said on Wednesday that
all things necessary will be done to make clear the circumstances
about the crash of the Air France Concorde supersonic aircraft on
Tuesday, which killed 113 people. (France-Chirac-Concorde Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan Wednesday said it shares the concern of
China and other countries that steps that can destabilize progress
towards disarmament and global nuclear stabilization should not be
taken. (Pakistan-US Missile)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KOTALIPARA -- Bangladeshi police so far has arrested thirteen
people who are suspected of being involved in bomb planting in
Kotalipara apparently to kill Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, a high
official said Wednesday. (Bangladesh-Arrest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- A French public prosecutor said Wednesday that the
crew of the Air France Concorde which crashed on Tuesday told the
control tower of Charles-de-Gaulle-Roissy airport that one of the
plane's left engines failed. (France-Concorde Crash-Engine)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The European Commission on Wednesday said that it
had approved special funds to cover the cost of clearing the
Danube within the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, where navigation
are blocked by debris of NATO bombed bridges. (EU-Danube-Funds)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat said on Wednesday in
Alexandria that the views came close between the Palestinians and
Israelis at the Camp David summit, although the two sides were
unable to reach a peace agreement on issues including Jerusalem.
(Egypt-Arafat-Camp David)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's Upper House Wednesday passed the Chemical
Weapons Convention Bill, 2000, to give effect to the Convention on
prohibition, development, production, stockpiling and use of
chemical weapons, to which India is a signatory. (India-Bill)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak arrived at the
Ben Gurion International Airport in Tel Aviv Wednesday afternoon
after 15 days of U.S.-brokered Camp David summit talks yielded no
peace agreement. 
