<HEADLINE> Romania's National Soccer Team to Have New Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 26 (Xinhua) -- A contract was struck assigning
Ladislau Boloni as first coach of Romania's senior national soccer
team, said a communique released on Wednesday by the Romanian
Soccer Federation.
</P>
<P>
The contract, which is valid from August 1, 2000 until July 31,
2002 aims to lead Romania to the final tournament of the 2002
World Cup Championships, said the communique.
</P>
<P>
Boloni, a former Romanian international player and coach of
Nancy's squad of France, will arrive in Bucharest on Monday and a
second coach of the national team will be named after his arrival.
</P>
<P>
Romania's former national coach Emeric Jenei will become a
technical director of the national teams (senior and junior). The
other technicians of the team will stay in place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
