<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FAO Official on Pakistani Food Autarky </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan can achieve autarky in
the food and cash crops and also become an exporter by exploiting
its potentialities in terms of good soil and abundant water
resources.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by Adil N. Aboul Naga, an official of the
United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO), the
Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We are happy that Pakistan reaped a good wheat crop this year.
It can not only sustain good production level in wheat but also
reap bumper crops of cotton, rice and oil seed," said Adil N.
Aboul Naga in a talk with APP.
</P>
<P>
He said that the development of an agriculture strategy for the
year 2010 can be helpful in achieving this long term goal.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Pakistani government is committed to the
development of the agriculture sector as Chief Executive General
Pervez Musharraf has termed agriculture one of the four top
priority areas of the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
