<HEADLINE> Barak's Meeting With Mubarak Postponed: PM Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak
has postponed his talks with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in
Egypt on the results of the Camp David summit until next week,
Barak's office said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Barak had been due to travel to Egyptian Mediterranean port city
of Alexandria on Friday to meet Mubarak, but the Israeli official
said the trip was postponed for "technical" reasons.
</P>
<P>
In Cairo, an official in Mubarak's office confirmed the
postponement.
</P>
<P>
The two-week-long three-way U.S.-Israeli-Palestinian summit
ended on Tuesday without reaching a framework agreement on final-
status issues such as the status of Jerusalem, borders, Palestinian
refugees and Jewish settlements.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat had stopped over in Alexandria
on Wednesday for talks with Mubarak on his way back home from the
summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
