<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Repairs Dam to Guard Against Overflowing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian authorities are
taking precautionary measures to repair dams to prevent flood
disasters which might occur in the current rainy season.
</P>
<P>
Renovation and embankment activities have been launched along
Awash riversides with a 4.5 million birr (about 560,000 U.S.
dollars) budget allocated by the federal government as a safeguard
against any eventuality of overflowing.
</P>
<P>
General Manager of the Awash Basin Water Resources
Administration Dawit Tefera said on Thursday that the repair of
the 23-km-long dam as well as clearing of silts have been underway.
</P>
<P>
Dawit said the overflowing of the Awash River, a major river in
central Ethiopia, has been effectively checked in the past due to
the launching of similar dam construction and silt clearing
activities.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that cotton and maize crops valued at over 30
million birr (3.74 million U.S. dollars) were destroyed due to the
overflowing of the river last year during which hundreds of
residents were also displaced.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
