<HEADLINE> Greece, Ukraine Initial Shipping Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Greece and Ukraine initialed here
Thursday a bilateral agreement to strengthen the shipping
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the pact, which was inked by Greece's Merchant Marine
Minister Christos Papoutsis and Deputy Transport Minister
Volodimir Sevriukov of Ukraine, the two countries will cooperate
on the basis of free and fair competition, the freedom of
navigation, and avoidance of unilateral measures that could have
an adverse impact on world maritime transport and trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
