<DOCNO> XIE20000727.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mushroom-Poisoning Death Toll Reaches 111 in Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A total of 111 people, among whom 27
were children, have died of mushroom poisoning since the beginning
of this year, the Interfax-Ukraine news agency quoted the Health
Ministry as saying Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that by Thursday, 1,094 cases of mushroom
poisoning have been registered in the country. The worst situation
was observed in the eastern Lugansk region, with 274 cases
reported, while in Donetsk 177 people were poisoned due to eating
wild mushroom.
</P>
<P>
With increasing mushroom poisoning and rising death toll, the
authorities are taking various measures to prevent similar
accidents. In Lugansk, police don't let residents enter forests to
go mushrooming. In Donetsk, selling mushroom is forbidden on the
markets if there is no sanitary inspection.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 200 mushroom poisoning cases were reported with only
one death. 
</P>
</TEXT>
