<HEADLINE> IDB Approves 150 Million Dollars Credit to Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Inter-American Development Bank (IDB)
has approved a 150 million dollar credit to Ecuador, where it'll
be meant for a program of economic reactivation and financing of
social development projects.
</P>
<P>
 Ecuador's Bank Superintendency said Thursday the outlay will
come through as soon as IDB and Ecuador's Ministry of Economy sign
corresponding covenants.
</P>
<P>
One of the projects benefited with the resources will creating
conditions for private participation in rehabilitating and
widening the electricity and telecommunication sectors.
</P>
<P>
The new credit is payable in 20 years, with five of grace, and
a variable interest rate beginning at 6.77 percent.
</P>
<P>
The resources will also be meant for agilizing sales of assets
of financial institutions intervened upon by the State.
</P>
<P>
According to bank superintendent, Juan Falconi, Ecaudor's
government is fulfilling its economic reactivation program set
with International Monetary Fund (IMF) and other international
organisms.
</P>
<P>
Before fulfillment of commitments, multilateral organisms has
provided Ecuador with financial assistance for 2.045 billion
dollars for the coming 3 years.  
