Agency (SANA) Fayez al-Sa'eg Director General of the General
Organization of Radio and Television to replace Adel Yazgy. Aly
Abdul-Karim, SANA Cairo Bureau Chief, will replace al-Sa'eg as SANA
Director General.
</P>
<P>
Under the decrees, Mahmoud Salamah (independent) will replace
Amid Kholy as director general of al-Wehda (unity) Publishing House
that issues al-Thawrah (the revolution) newspaper. Kholy used to
hold the post for 23 years.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Khalaf Mohammed al-Jarad has been nominated director general
of Teshrin Publishing House that issues Teshrin newspaper to
replace Muhammad Khairal-Wadi who held the position for more than
20 years.
</P>
<P>
Al-Jarad has a doctorate in philosophy from Russia and is a
member of the Arab Writers Association and a scholar with the
Strategic Studies Center, Damascus University.
</P>
<P>
The decrees also nominate Dr. Mohammed al-Nasoury director
general of the Syrian Arab Distribution Organization to replace Aly
Isa who has retired.
</P>
<P>
The most significant among the new nominations is the nomination
of Mahmoud Salamah, who has not party affiliation and does not
belong to Syrian press profession, director general of al-Wehda
Publishing House, while all the other nominees belong to the ruling
Arab Socialist Baath Party (ASBP).
</P>
<P>
Turky Sakr, chief editor of al-Baath daily - the mouthpiece of
the ASBP, retained his position. 
</P>
