<HEADLINE> 19 Russian Servicemen Killed in Chechnya in Past Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen Russian federal servicemen
were killed and 94 wounded in the week to Thursday in the
breakaway republic of Chechnya, a ranking officer said.
</P>
<P>
During this period, five Defense Ministry servicemen were
killed and 34 wounded, and 14 Interior Ministry servicemen were
killed and 60 wounded, the Interfax news agency reported, quoting
Colonel General Valery Manilov, first deputy head of the General
Staff.
</P>
<P>
The figures brought to 2,537 the number of federal servicemen
killed in the North Caucasus since last August. The total number
of the wounded stood at 8,050.
</P>
<P>
Russia's military campaign against separatist rebels came after
two waves of armed Chechen incursions into neighboring Dagestan
and a series of apartment explosions that left over 300 people
dead and numerous wounded in Moscow and two other cities.
</P>
<P>
During the military operations in Chechnya, 2,259 servicemen of
the federal forces have been killed and 6,366 wounded since
October 1 of last year, Interfax said.
</P>
<P>
On the separatists' side, Manilov said, more than 60 rebels,
including "several prominent fighters and mercenaries" were
eliminated by federal forces over the past week.
</P>
<P>
Federal units discovered and eliminated some 30 rebel camps, 25
dugouts and "a dozen caches" in the course of search and
reconnaissance operations in the period, Manilov said.
</P>
<P>
The total number of rebels "on the whole territory of Chechnya
amounts to about 2,000," Manilov said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
