<HEADLINE> One Copt Shot Dead, Three Others Wounded in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 27 (Xinhua) -- One Copt was killed and three others
were wounded in an attack perpetrated by an assailant in the south
of the Egyptian capital of Cairo, the Interior Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Fakhri Ayyad Mussaad and three employees were unloading eggs at
Mussaad's chicken farm in Sul village, 60 kilometers south of
Cairo, when a gunman opened fire on them, killing Mussaad
instantly, the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The three others were taken to a hospital. It is not immediately
known how seriously they were wounded.
</P>
<P>
The four victims were all Coptic Christians, but the ministry
has ruled out an attack by Islamic militants, saying investigations
have revealed the incident was prompted by a land dispute between
the deceased and others in his village.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has a population of 64 million, of whom over nine percent
are Christians. It witnessed the worst sectarian violence in 20
years, in which 22 people died, most of them Coptic Christians, in
clashes that broke out due to business disputes last January in the
town of Kosheh in Suhag Governorate, 400 kilometers south of Cairo.
</P>
