<HEADLINE> Halifax Group Enjoys Profits Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Halifax Group has reported a 21
percent increase in profits during the first half of the year
despite increased competition.
</P>
<P>
Net lending in the mortgage business has doubled to 2.4 billion
pounds (1.6 billion U.S. dollars) compared to the same period last
year, giving Halifax, the largest building society in Britain, a
market share of 12 percent.
</P>
<P>
Gross lending, before mortgage redemptions and repayments, was
also strong, at 10 billion pounds (6.6 billion dollars), giving a
market share of 17 percent, slightly up on 16 percent the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
Despite the glowing figures, Halifax warned that the
competition was fierce and that growth in demand was slowing.
</P>
<P>
Chief executive Jame Crosby said there was increasing pressure
on margins as the group fought to compete with existing rivals and
new entrants such as e-banks offering lower rates to attract
customers.
</P>
<P>
Halifax was doing well at watching costs and had beaten its
zero cost-growth target, Crosby added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
