<HEADLINE> Russia Witnesses 10 Contract Killings Each Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Interior Ministry said
Thursday that 249 contract killings were registered in the first
half of this year, and the rate amounts to 10.3 contract killings
every week during the period.
</P>
<P>
General Vyacheslav Trubnikov, chief of the ministry's Criminal
Investigation Department, said 49 contract murders were solved in
the first six months of this year, the Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
He said many of the contract killings were related to the
victims' business activities and in 37 percent of the cases, the
contractors were related to the victim. They are mainly the
cofounders of companies, debtors or deputies of the killed.
</P>
<P>
Contract killings for domestic reasons are mainly ordered by
close relatives -- wives, husbands or children. Such cases account
for about one quarter of all those registered, Trubnikov said.
</P>
