The Fijian army arrested hundreds of supporters of Speight on
Thursday, risking to plunge the island country into a civil war.
</P>
<P>
In a primary action of retaliation, the coup supporters took a
plane of Air Fiji and detained two pilots of New Zealand
nationality.
</P>
<P>
The rebels have also detained 50 Fijians of Indian origin in
barracks. 
