<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Urges Creation of Public Finance System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing today
called for speeding up the establishment of a public finance
system that can meet the needs of China's swift economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee,
said at a national finance conference that building a stable,
balanced and powerful national finance is necessary for
guaranteeing the sound development of China's economy and various
social undertakings.
</P>
<P>
He said that financial work should also focus on the
fundamental interests of the broad masses of the people.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier said the public finance system should
guarantee the timely distribution of basic subsidies for laid-off
workers of the State-owned enterprises, pensions for retirees and
subsistence allowances for urban residents under the poverty line.
</P>
<P>
He said the priorities of the financial work is to guarantee
necessary public expenditure, adjust the relationship of revenue
and distribution, enhance social security, and promote fair and
orderly market competition.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier also called for continued efforts to ensure
the implementation of the budget for the year. 
</P>
