<HEADLINE> Japan Donates to Schools in S.W. China's Guizhou Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, July 27 (Xinhua)-- Japan's Grassroots Ground Aid
donated some 740,000 yuan to primary schools in four impoverished
villages in Ziyun County of Southwest China's Guizhou Province
today.
</P>
<P>
As many as 1,200 children, more than half of whom have been
studying in run down houses, will benefit from the program.
</P>
<P>
Ziyun County, with ethnic minority people making up most of the
population, desperately needs funding to develop its education
programs because of the underdeveloped economy.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Grassroots Ground Aid, which has been cooperating with
China for more than ten years, grants free aid and support for
selected programs in the fields of culture, education, and health
protection to underdeveloped countries and regions. 
