<HEADLINE> IBM, Top Chinese Universities Launch Research Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The global computer giant IBM and
China's elite Qinghua University and Beijing University jointly
established a research institute early this month.
</P>
<P>
IBM will provide equipment, researchers and most of the
operating expenses, while the Chinese partners will be responsible
for office buildings, labs, teachers and students.
</P>
<P>
A special committee composed of people from the both sides has
been formed to manage the institute, which will mainly focus on e-
business. The administration of the institute will be handled by
the two schools.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will share the intellectual property rights of
the achievements.
</P>
<P>
"It's a good opportunity for us to cooperate with the well-
known international company," said Gong Ke, vice-president of
Qinghua. 
