<HEADLINE> Authorities Tipped Off on Illegal Entertainment Sites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Culture announced
that it has received 129 telephone tip-offs from various
localities about illegal activities in entertainment places.
</P>
<P>
The reports, concerning 49 video arcades, 21 karaoke halls, and
other places, came from 26 provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions including Beijing, Shaanxi, Shandong, Henan,
Jiangsu and Hunan, Guangming Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
Tipsters said the places are involved in prostitution, gambling
and receiving underage customers, the nationwide newspaper
reported.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper, the ministry will order local
administrative bodies to severely punish people who violate the
law, but did not elaborate on the form of punishment.
</P>
<P>
Together with police and other departments, the Ministry of
Culture on June 30 launched a three-month crackdown on
entertainment sites throughout the country. 
</P>
