<HEADLINE> Beijingers' Home-buying Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The home-buying of residents in
Beijing continues to rise, with 2.2 million square meters of
housing sold during the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Beijing Municipal Development Planning
Commission, Beijingers spent 8.36 billion yuan (one billion U.S.
dollars) to buy housing in the six-month period, 2.4 times that of
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
About 80 percent of the buyers are individuals instead of
corporation groups. The commission said this is the result of the
improvement in housing subsidies and bank services.
</P>
<P>
The commission said the government will continue to keep prices
at the local real estate market prices at an appropriate level in
the second half of this year, and renovation of dilapidated
housing will be stepped up to ensure the completion of eight
million square meters of housing space this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
