<HEADLINE> Eight People Arrested for Deadly Bus Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Eight people who prosecutors say
are responsible for a bus accident which killed 79 people on July
7 in the southwestern China city of Liuzhou have been arrested.
</P>
<P>
Hao Zhizhen, former director of the fourth engineering office
of the Liuzhou Urban Utility Maintenance Department, and Wu Zheng,
Luo Maoliang and Li Shuhua, workers and safety officers of the
department, are in custody for failing to adequately supervise
workers on a bridge repair project, indirectly contributing to the
tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Pan Tianming, Pan Yanyang, Peng Changheng and Liu Heping, all
temporary workers with the department, allegedly directly caused
the accident, according to a city prosecutor.
</P>
<P>
On the day of the accident, Hao Zhizhen, Wu Zheng, Luo Maoliang
and Li Shuhua, who were overseeing the safety and quality of
repair work on Hudong Bridge, did not go to the work site to
supervise their maintenance men, leaving the four alone to do the
job.
</P>
<P>
According to the prosecutor, the four workers failed to remove
cement partitions from the Hudong Bridge after finishing their
work. That night, a bus with the Liuzhou bus company crashed into
the cement partitions and lost control, plunging into the river.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
