<HEADLINE> 50 Missing in Launch Capsize in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- About 50 people were reported
missing Thursday after a launch, hit by two others, capsized in
the Buriganga river in Narayanganj district, some 20 kilometers
east of Dhaka, the United News of Bangladesh reported.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said the ill-fated launch, MV Ashique, with some
100 passengers on board, was knocked from side by another Launch,
MV Pintu-2, when it was changing its course to the mainstream of
the river.
</P>
<P>
Within a minute, yet another launch, Sagar-5, rammed against MV
Ashique, forcing it to sink into the mid-river. Of the passengers,
some 50 swam ashore, and another 50 were still missing, police and
witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
Rescue operation started immediately after the mishap, but the
rescuers could not trace any body or salvage the launch till 4:30
p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
