<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Pak Up 8 Percent in Last Fiscal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Net foreign investment during
1999-2000 in Pakistan's private sector amounted to 543 million U.S.
dollars against 499.6 million dollars in the previous year,
showing an increase of over 8 percent, the State Bank of Pakistan
(SBP) reported.
</P>
<P>
Direct investment totaled 467 million dollars and portfolio
investment 73.5 million against the previous year of 472 million
and 27.3 million, respectively, according to the figures released
by the SBP.
</P>
<P>
Portfolio investment registered a 250 percent increase despite
the turbulence in the stock exchange during the outgoing year.
</P>
<P>
The SBP said that direct investment from the UK was at the top
with 169 million dollars as against the U.S. investment of 166.9
million dollars. 
</P>
