<HEADLINE> 3 Filipino Teenagers Sentenced for Raping 12-Year-Old Girl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Three Filipino youngsters were
sentenced here Thursday by a local court to a jail term of seven
to 14 years for raping a 12-year old girl in Quezon city, Metro
Manila, two years ago, a judge said.
</P>
<P>
Quezon City Regional Trial Court Judge Jose Catral-Mendoza
handed down the sentence to the three youngsters, who will have to
stay at the Boy's Town in Marikina city here for their
rehabilitation and to serve their punishment.
</P>
<P>
"Considering that at the time of the commission of the offense,
the three accused were under 18 years of age, they are entitled to
the privileged mitigating circumstance of minority," Mendoza said.
</P>
<P>
Rape, if committed by adults, is usually meted with life
imprisonment, according to related Philippine laws. 
</P>
