<HEADLINE> Romania Records More Foreign Exchange Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Foreign Exchange reserves of Romania's Central Bank increased
by 400 million U.S. dollars thanks to funds coming from the
International Monetary Fund, the World Bank and the European Union.
</P>
<P>
An additional 100 million U.S. dollars is expected to come this
week from the World Bank as contribution to an adjustment program
for the country's agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
Gold reserves of the Central Bank neared 970 million U.S.
dollars at the end of July, Curentul said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, foreign trade deficit fell to 417 million U.S.
dollars, a decrease by 170 million U.S. dollars compared with the
same period of 1999.
</P>
<P>
According to local analysts, these positive trends give reasons
for encouragement and the reserves are expected to reach 2.5
billion U.S. dollars by the end of the year. 
