<HEADLINE> Yangtze River Water Level Dropping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The water level in the main artery
of the Yangtze River is out of the danger zone for flooding,
according to the latest information from the Yangtze River Flood
Control Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three days there were only light showers but no
heavy rain over China's longest river.
</P>
<P>
At 8 a.m. today, the water level at the river section of Wuhan,
capital of central China's Hubei Province, dropped to 24.42 meters.
</P>
<P>
The local hydrometeorological bureau reported that the water
flow at Yichang will continue to decrease in the next three days,
and is expected to slow to 15,500 cubic meters per second on July
30. Similarly, Yangtze water flow at Wuhan and Datong will
continue to lose speed in the same period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
