<HEADLINE> China to Speed Up Development of Advanced Particle Accelerator Device </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The State Council has approved
plans for the development of advanced particle accelerator and
high-energy physics submitted by the Chinese Academy of Sciences (
CAS).
</P>
<P>
At the seventh meeting of the Science and Technology Leading
Group of the State Council held here today, plans for 12 important
high-tech programs in the following five years were also approved.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting was presided over by Zhu Rongji, China's
premier and the head of the group.
</P>
<P>
The 12 high-tech programs include construction of a high-speed
information network, super computers, a digital high-density
television system, biological chips, and a high-speed railway.
</P>
<P>
A State Council official said that the development of advanced
particle accelerator and high-energy physics is vital for raising
the level of science and technology in China.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will solicit advice on how to carry out
the projects from Chinese and overseas experts.
</P>
<P>
The official said now that feasibility studies have been
completed by the State Development Planning Commission and other
departments, and the 12 high-tech programs are expected to be
listed in the draft of China's 10th five-year development plan
from 2001 to 2005. 
</P>
</TEXT>
