<HEADLINE> France to Hold Religious Mourning Ceremony for Concorde Crash Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A multi-confessional religious
service will be held at 17:30 (15:30 GMT) Thursday at the
Madeleine church in central Paris to memorize the 113 people who
died in the crash of the Air France Concorde supersonic aircraft
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Four religious confessions -- Catholicism, Protestantism,
Orthodoxy and Judaism -- will join the ceremony which will be
attended by French Interior Minister Jean-Pierre Chevenement,
French Minister of Transport Jean-Claude Gayssot, German Foreign
Minister Joschka Fischer and German Transport Minister Reinhard
Klimmt.
</P>
<P>
During the ceremony, the Bible will be read in both French and
German, said the organizers of the service.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, all the planes will stop taking off for one minute
at the two international airports of Paris when the religious
ceremony begins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
