<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Maybank to Start Operation in Shanghai in Early 2001 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Malayan Banking Bhd (Maybank),
Malaysia's largest bank, said Thursday its branch in Shanghai,
China, is expected to be fully operational by January 1 next year.
</P>
<P>
The bank has received approval from the People's Bank of China
to operate a branch in Shanghai, making it the first Malaysian
bank to operate a branch there, it said in a statement issued here.
</P>
<P>
This will be Maybank's second office in China, the first being
a representative office in Beijing opened in 1993.
</P>
<P>
"Our proposed branch operations in China will better support
our customers both from Malaysia as well as other locations that
we operate in, who have trade and investment links with China,
particularly in Shanghai which is the main commercial and
financial center there," the bank's managing director Amirsham A
Aziz said in the statement.
</P>
<P>
The branch will provide a full range of foreign currency
denominated banking services including loans and advances,
treasury, trade financing, remittances, deposits and selected
retail products.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian largest banking group's enhanced presence in
China will also enable it to better facilitate trade and
investment between Malaysia and China, the statement said.
</P>
