<HEADLINE> Guangdong Ensures Quality of Water for Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province in south
China has ensured good quality of water supply to Hong Kong,
according a meeting on protecting the Dongjiang-Shenzhen water
supply system here today.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong pipes 1.1 billion cu m of water from the Dongjiang, a
tributary of the Pearl River to Hong Kong every year. The river is
also the major drinking water source for Shenzhen, a commercial
center in Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
To keep the water from contamination, cities along the river
invested 430 million yuan (51.8 million US dollars) from 1993 to
1999 and the provincial government injected another 290 million
yuan (34.9 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
There are 51 monitoring centers along the river. They reported
that the river water is up to the state's standard for first- and
second-class water quality since 1995.
</P>
<P>
Heyuan City seated on the bank of Dongjiang adds more than 34,
000 ha of afforestation area every year along the river.
</P>
<P>
The economic zone of Shenzhen located at the lower reaches of
the river plans to spend 42 million yuan (5 million US dollars)
combating soil erosion along the river annually in the next five
years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
