<HEADLINE> Mental Disorders Hotbed for "Falun Gong": Expert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Stress, nervousness, anxiety and
mental disorder have provided a hotbed the "Falun Gong" cult in
China.
</P>
<P>
Wang Qingren, a professor with the Central University for
Nationalities, made the remarks today during an exclusive
interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Accustomed to the cradle-to-grave employment, many people found
it hard to adapt themselves quickly to the increased pressure and
intensified competition of modern life, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Dazzled by the self-claimed "Savior" Li Hongzhi, people turned
to him for guidance to regain their inner balance and stability,
Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Seeking help from Falun Gong rather than a professional
psychiatrist reveals that many people are suffering from various
kinds of mental disorders, said Wang. 
</P>
