<HEADLINE> Austrian Artist's Works to Be Shown in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A photo and painting show of Eva
Choung-Fux, called "Survivors on Life", will be opened in the
Shanghai Library from August 4 to 27.
</P>
<P>
On show will be 500 photography and photographic works on
canvas, 32 original and print works, and 32 oil paintings Choung-
Fux produced between 1984 and 2000.
</P>
<P>
Born in Vienna, 1935, this world renowned Austrian artist
graduated from the Academy of the Applied Arts in Vienna.
</P>
<P>
After graduation, she spends seven years in Tokyo and Seoul.
</P>
<P>
"I enjoy a deep friendship, respect and love for artists from
many countries," said Choung-Fux.
</P>
<P>
In early 1990s, Choung-Fux drove around ten European countries
to interview World War Two survivors and their offspring.
</P>
<P>
She created a great number of oil paintings, prints and
watercolors, among which 500 will be shown at the show.  
</P>
</TEXT>
