<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Continues Stronger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended above
59 U.S. cents Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the Australian dollar was at 59.22 U.S. cents
from 58.76 the previous day.
</P>
<P>
There are speculation that the Reserve Bank of Australia will
consider lifting official interest rates come September with
growing inflationary pressures.
</P>
<P>
There is less hope for the currency to go through the level of
60 U.S. cents in the near future because it is too vulnerable to
outside's shocks. Economists realized the real reason for the
weakness of the Australian dollars is the country's high debt.
</P>
