<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ARF FMs Hail Positive Developments on Korean Peninsula </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministers attending the
7th Association of Southeast Asian Nations Regional Forum (ARF)
here Thursday expressed their satisfaction with the positive
developments on the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
In the Chairman Statement released at the closing of the annual
meeting, the ministers voiced their belief that the on-going
momentum of inter-Korean dialogue and interaction would be carried
forward with a view to achieving lasting peace and eventual
reunification on the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The ministers praised in particular the historic inter-Korean
summit in June and voiced their support to the North-South Joint
Declaration reached at the summit.
</P>
<P>
They also appreciated increased dialogue and exchanges between
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and several ARF
countries, while welcoming the participation for the first time of
the DPRK in the forum.
</P>
<P>
They expressed their hopes for further efforts by all parties
concerned within the framework of inter-Korea dialogue, the US-
DPRK and Japan-DPRK talks, the Four-Party Talks and broader
international efforts.
</P>
<P>
ARF, now comprising ten ASEAN member states, Papua New Guinea,
the only ASEAN observer, ten dialogue partners, Mongolia and DPRK,
serves as a multilateral consultative mechanism for peace and
security issues in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
DPRK was recently granted a full membership of ARF. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000727.0179 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India, Russia to Set Up Commission on Military-Technical  Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a statement on his recent visit to Russia to the Lok Sabha,
or the Indian parliament, Fernandes said that the joint commission
would be at the level of defense minister on the Indian side and
deputy prime minister on the Russian side.
</P>
<P>
The Indian defense minister told the parliament that during his
visit, he had detailed discussions with Russian leaders, including
Deputy Prime Minister Ilya Klebanov and Defense Minister Igor
Sergeyev, on various aspects of the two countries' bilateral
relations, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
"The important issues taken up included acquisition of new
modern weapon systems, platforms and equipment which would
significantly enhance the capability of India's armed forces and
which will have a major force multiplier effect," Fernandes was
quoted as saying. 
</P>
