<HEADLINE> 75 Stowaways Caught in Northeastern Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Frontier police in Dalian, a port
city in northeast China, has cracked a human trafficking gang and
caught 75 stowaways.
</P>
<P>
The "snakeheads" or human smugglers had stowaways from
northeastern Heilongjiang and Jilin provinces at the Dalian port
on July 15, and the 75 boarded a small wooden fish boat at 1:00 am
on July 20, the police have found.
</P>
<P>
When the police stopped the boat on July 25, all of the 75 on
board were crowded in a less than ten-sq-m compartment. They had
not eaten for three days.
</P>
<P>
All of them would pay the snakeheads 40,000 yuan to 60,000 yuan
(about 4,800 U.S. dollars to 7,200 U.S. dollars) once they got to
the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
Another 144 stowaways were caught in three recent cases on July
18, 19 and 21, all trying to get to the Republic of Korea.
</P>
</TEXT>
