<HEADLINE> China Sets up Internet Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The China Internet Committee was
officially set up today.
</P>
<P>
Under the supervision of the China Information Economy
Association, sponsors include gateway websites and e-commerce
websites Sina, Sohu and 8848, and media websites such as Xinhuanet.
com and CCTV.com.
</P>
<P>
The committee will regularly call in IT entrepreneurs and
experts to discuss the direction of Internet developments.
</P>
<P>
The committee will also provide opportunities for international
exchange and training courses for personnel in the industry.
