<HEADLINE> CASS Obtains State Funding for 50 Academic Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Researchers with the Chinese
Academy of Social Sciences (CASS) have obtained state funding
worth 2.59 million yuan (312,000 U.S. dollars) for 50 academic
projects carried out this year.
</P>
<P>
Average funds for each academic project this year range from 40,
000 to 55,000 yuan, an official said. Meanwhile, the academy
itself will add another 25 percent for each project.
</P>
<P>
Many well-known scholars are focusing on practical issues
including Chinese investment in foreign countries, macro-control
of the economy during deflation, the influence to China's industry
after entry into the World Trade Organization (WTO), the WTO and
China's intellectual property protection.
</P>
<P>
CASS encourages its researchers to apply for financial support
from the National Social Sciences Fund and will provide money for
them to take part in international academic exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Among the 7,066 applicants nationwide this year, 650 received
support from the national fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
