<HEADLINE> Indonesian President Urged to Uncover July Riots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Abdurrahman
Wahid was strongly urged here Thursday to soon bring former
President Soeharto and those were allegedly involved in the bloody
July 27 riots four years ago to justice.
</P>
<P>
The demand was made by supporters of the Indonesian Democratic
Party of Struggle (PDI Perjuangan) when commemorating the 4th
anniversary of attacking the party's headquarters by the then
government-backed rivals.
</P>
<P>
They asked the president to launch a comprehensive probe into
the bloody incident and try those were allegedly involved,
including former President Soeharto and other military officials.
</P>
<P>
"Soeharto has to be brought to justice to account for his deed
in the July riots," a protester screamed, while the others voiced
their demands at the former military officials who were also
allegedly involved in the riots which believed to have killed
dozens of lives at that time.
</P>
<P>
The protesters named incumbent Governor of Jakarta Sutiyoso who
was Jakarta military commander and former Indonesia military (TNI)
chief Feisal Tandjung as the most responsible persons over the
riots.
</P>
<P>
After staging a ceremony at the front yard of the former PDI'
headquarters on Jl. Diponegoro, Central Jakarta, on Thursday
morning, the protesters then marched toward Soeharto's and
Sutiyoso's residences, but no clashes were reported during the
protest which backed by some student movements such as the
National Students League for Democracy (LMND), the Democratic
Peoples Party (PRD) and the Anti-New Order Regime Front. 
</P>
</TEXT>
