<DOCNO> XIE20000727.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Promote ARF to be Effective, Relevant Forum: ARF FMs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
They made this clear in the Chairman's Statement issued after
the closing of the forum here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, they said that they intend to follow an
evolutionary approach towards the development of ARF role that,
they hoped, will proceed from "confidence-building" at first, then
to "preventive diplomacy," and finally to "elaboration of
approaches to conflict."
</P>
<P>
They in particular underscored the significance of confidence-
building, saying that it is a foundation and primary focus of ARF.
Confidence-building, they noted, will ensure the effective
implementation of related agreements or understandings reached by
its members and will meaningfully augment "the comfort level,
trust, confidence and understanding as well as cooperation" among
its members.
</P>
<P>
Agreeing that ARF continue to move at a pace comfortable to all
its members, they nevertheless pledged that ARF will play its role
"as driving force" in regional peace and security, and will work
to evolve consensus on vital subjects of Asia-Pacific security.
</P>
<P>
ARF is an organ of ASEAN designed for promotion of confidence,
understanding and cooperation among its participants on the
security issues. It was initiated in 1993 and its members include
foreign minister of ASEAN, its dialogue partners and other
entities. China became its full member in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
