<DOCNO> XIE20000727.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Contributes to Regional Peace, Stability and Development: Tang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 27 (Xinhua) -- History has and will continue to
prove that China is a positive factor and major force in
safeguarding peace and promoting development, Chinese Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Since we last met at this Forum, China has made new
contributions to peace, stability and development in the Asia-
Pacific region, " he said in his speech at the annual gathering of
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations Regional Forum (ARF).
</P>
<P>
China has been vigorously pressing ahead with its reform and
opening-up, and its economy has maintained a fairly rapid growth
while taking a favorable and important turn, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-Strait relations, he said that China has firmly
implemented the fundamental principle of "peaceful reunification
and one country, two systems" and President Jiang Zemin's eight-
point proposal on the question of Taiwan, and worked hard to
advance the cause of peaceful reunification of China.
</P>
<P>
Working continuously to develop goodneighborly and friendly
relations with its surrounding countries, China has signed or
issued documents on bilateral cooperation oriented towards the
21st century with most of the ASEAN member states, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the process of "Shanghai Five", namely, China,
Russia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan, is "moving toward
in a sound manner and playing a significant role in promoting
regional and world peace and stability".
</P>
<P>
The active participation in East Asian cooperation and other
regional as well as international cooperation, he stressed, has
further strengthened the mutually beneficial cooperation between
China and other countries in Asia and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
"We have always been supportive of the ARF dialogue and
cooperation, and actively participated in and successfully
implemented a number of Confidence-Building Measures (CBM)
Projects," he said.
</P>
<P>
As a permanent member of the United Nations Security Council
and a country in the Asia-pacific region, China will continue to
perform its duty in promoting peace and stability in the region
and the world at large, he added.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, China became a full member of ARF, which serves as a
multilateral consultative forum aimed at promoting preventive
diplomacy and confidence building among the nations in the Asia-
Pacific region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
