<HEADLINE> Milosevic Likely to Move to Parma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rome, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav striker Savo Milosevic has
arrived in Parma for a medical examination and is expected to
transfer to the Serie A club from Spain's Real Zaragoza later on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic, had agreed to sign a four-year contract with Parma,
according to reports by Italian media on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic scored five goals for Yugoslavia at Euro 2000, making
him joint top scorer in the tournament along with Dutch striker
Patrick Kluivert.
</P>
<P>
Last season Milosevic scored 19 goals in 30 league games for
Zaragoza and has been the target of transfer speculation
throughout the close season.
</P>
<P>
A powerfully-built forward, Milosevic began his career with
Partizan Belgrade. After scoring 74 goals in 98 games for the
Yugoslav club, he moved to English premier league side Aston Villa.
</P>
<P>
Following three largely disappointing seasons with the
Birmingham club he went to Zaragoza in the summer of 1998 and
quickly rediscovered his form. 
</P>
</TEXT>
