<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Capital Iron and Steel Company Shifts to Hi-Tech Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- By the year 2010 iron and steel
will no longer be the pillar products of the Beijing-based Capital
Iron and Steel Company (CISC), also known as Shougang, when its
sales volume of high and new technological products reaches 50
percent.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Jimin, general manager, said the enterprise will first
lower iron and steel output from today's eight million tons to six
million tons in two years. Non-iron or steel output value will
exceed 50 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
CISC will use its two million sq m of land in the downtown area
for real estate and service industries. It is also planning to
establish a complete microelectronics production chain from chip
designing and manufacturing to computer production.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to expand its business in Asia, Europe and
America by making use of the Hong Kong stock market.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said their steel and iron company in Peru is progressing
smoothly. The joint venture in Zimbabwe is also running smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the company's chips for electronic watches and TV
remote controllers now occupy 50 percent of the domestic market.
Robots, touch-screen computers, and auto air-conditioners also
have a bright future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000727.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Increase in Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Shandong Province, China's No. 3
powerful economic powerhouse, earned 11.38 billion US dollars in
foreign trade in the first half of the year, a rise of more than
37 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The total included 7.05 billion US dollars in exports, up 37.6
percent on 1999 figure, and 4.33 billion US dollars in imports, up
37.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Exports in June alone hit a record high of 1.46 billion US
dollars, a 52.5 percent rise from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Local exports to Asia saw a year-on-year 38.5 percent rise to 4.
15 billion US dollars from January to June this year, and the
volume to EU increased 36.8 percent to 970 million US dollars. The
volume to the U.S. rose 35 percent to 1.34 billion US dollars, and
that to the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) rose by 58
percent.
</P>
<P>
Shandong exported 3.39 billion US dollars of goods through
general trade in the six-month period, up 40.6 percent on a yearly
basis, while processing trade exports rose 34.7 percent to 3.63
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Manufactured goods accounted for nearly 80 percent of local
exports, or 5.56 billion US dollars, up 1.6 percent on 1999 level.
</P>
<P>
The province exported 1.45 billion US dollars of machinery and
electronic products, up 52.8 percent on last year's figure.
</P>
