<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Mix Improved In Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investment mix in east
China's Fujian Province has steadily improved. Sixty percent of
overseas investment introduced locally this year is from Europe,
the U.S. and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Fujian Province has got investments from more than 70 countries
and regions.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment in local service trade reported a big
increase in the first half of the year, with commerce and catering
figures rising 31 percent and that in social service soaring by 91
percent.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded enterprises increased 620 million US dollars of
investment from January to June this year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, Fujian had 27,000 overseas-funded
enterprises, using 61.7 billion US dollars of contractual overseas
money. Of these enterprises, 16,000 enterprises have become
operational. 
</P>
