<HEADLINE> China's T-bond Trade Expands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua)-- China's treasuries stayed stable
today. Of the six current bonds, one slid slightly, two saw tame
rises, while the remaining half closed unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Trading value today was 1.41 billion yuan, up 135 million as
compared to yesterday, according to Homeway, China's leading on-
line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Both 009704 and 010004, the new ten-year floating-rate bond,
picked up by 0.07 percent. However, the former witnessed a thin
trade volume of 33 million yuan, indicating the slack buying
interest.
</P>
<P>
009908 edged down 0.03 percent to 102.13 yuan, accompanied by a
big turnover of 937 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The stock composite indices closed at new record highs today,
so it is difficult for the T-bonds to turn active. However, the
expanding turnover on bonds may suggest that some conservative
investors begin to add treasuries in their assets portfolios amid
concerns for potential correction in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The combined turnover of three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-
day repo transactions amounted to 5.31 billion yuan, four times
the figure for the previous trading day. 
</P>
