Armed Forces of the Philippines, confirmed President Estrada wants
the Civilian Armed Forces Geographical Unit (CAFGU) activated on
August 1.
</P>
<P>
Reyes said 70 percent of the total CAFGU force or 7,000 will be
deployed in Mindanao to combat rebels' insurgency and promote
peace efforts in the area, while the remaining 30 percent or 3,000
will be assigned in Luzon and Visayas.
</P>
<P>
"We need the CAFGU so that peace efforts would also be
accelerated," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The deployment will enable us to protect communities from the
Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) terroristic activities and to
ensure that the rehabilitation efforts will be unhampered," Reys
said. 
