<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese FM on Future Role of ARF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan talked about the future role the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations Regional Forum (ARF) should play in regional
security, which he stressed is of great interest to all people.
</P>
<P>
"In fact, the ARF clearly defined its functions upon its
inception, i.e. the forum is designed to enhance dialogue,
increase cooperation, bridge differences, and promote constructive
relations between its members, " he said in his speech at the 7th
ARF meeting here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He noted that over the past six years, the ARF has played a
positive role in enhancing dialogue, understanding and cooperation,
and has gradually formed an operational mechanism of its own.
</P>
<P>
"The mechanism has made the ARF attractive as ever, " he said,
"its membership is increasing, and the approach it has initiated
is winning increasing support of the people."
</P>
<P>
He hereby welcomed the formal entry of the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) into the forum.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, as the ARF enters its seventh year, issues
such as where it should go and how it should develop are again
placed on the Forum's agenda.
</P>
<P>
Tang said China agrees that the ARF should continuously move
forward towards its set objectives, and hopes that it will, in the
light of the region's feature of diversity, further strengthen
dialogue, enhance mutual understanding and trust between its
members, while helping to foster in the region a security
mentality and model that confirms to the trend of the times.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side agrees to the idea that the ARF should
consolidate and deepen the confidence-building measures and, at
the same time, explore and discuss the question of preventive
diplomacy in the region," he said.
</P>
<P>
The 23-member ARF is now the biggest inter-governmental forum
for security dialogue and cooperation in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
