<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Big Rise of Overseas Investment In Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The number of overseas-funded
enterprises in east China's Shandong Province increased by 1,181
in the first half of the year, according to the provincial foreign
trade and economic cooperation bureau.
</P>
<P>
Among the newly-approved enterprises, 85 cost more than 10
million US dollars each and involved 1.32 billion US dollars in
contractual overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The province introduced more than 2.4 billion US dollars of
contractual overseas investment from January to June, a rise of 81
percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
Some 57 percent of the investment, or 1.38 billion US dollars,
flowed into Qingdao, a local major coastal city. Qingdao approved
the establishment of more than 480 overseas-funded projects in the
six-month period, up 63 percent from last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao has joined hands with a British company to set up a
local container harbor company costing 177 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Qingdao Qianwan Container Harbor Company used 86.61 million
US dollars of contractual overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Among the world's top 500 transnationals, 79 have invested in
Shandong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
