<DOCNO> XIE20000727.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Make Community Service Major Source of Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China has decided to make the
community service sector a major source of jobs for laid-off
workers in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Zuoji, Minister of Labor and Social Security, said here
recently that China will take measures to further develop
community service and help more laid-off workers get re-employed.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that an increasing number of workers are being laid
off this year although 4.92 million of the 6.52 million laid-off
workers found new jobs last year.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang, China's community service sector now merely
contributes 3.9 percent of the country's employment, compared with
20 percent to 30 percent in developed countries.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey shows that the urban community service sector
in China boasts more than 15 million potential jobs.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in the past few years some 40 percent of
the laid-off workers that have found new jobs are employed in the
community service sector.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
