<HEADLINE> China Vying for Internatinal Engineering Contracting Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China has made great headway in
expanding presence in the international engineering contracting
markets and was listed among the top ten engineering contractors
in the world, according to today's China Construction News.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said that China undertook a large number of
construction projects in various countries and regions worldwide
in 1999, with contract volume and business turnover hitting 13
billion US dollars and 11.23 billion US dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 20 years, China's cumulative overseas engineering
contract volume and business turnover amounted to 96.469 billion
US dollars and 60.6 billion US dollars, respectively, with the
annual increase rate hitting 31.1 percent and 23.3 percent.
</P>
