<HEADLINE> Philippine Manufacturing Output Up in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Philippine manufacturing output in
May rose 12.3 percent year-on-year by volume and increased 20.65
percent by value, after slowing down since December last year, the
National Statistics Office (NSO) said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In its monthly integrated survey of selected industries, the
NSO said manufacturing sales rose 22.5 percent in May year-on-year
in terms of volume and grew 34.2 percent by value.
</P>
<P>
According to the NSO, the year-on-year drop in April in output
of 4 percent in terms of volume was revised Thursday to an
increase of 0.1 percent while the 3.6 percent rise in production
by value was revised to a 6.8 percent growth. 
</P>
