<HEADLINE> Brazil Beat Argentina 3-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazil ended Argentina's
winning record by beating its arch-rivals 3-1 in a World Cup
qualifier on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Brazil made six changes to the team which went down by 1-2 to
Paraguay last week. One of the newcomers, striker Alex, scored
the first goal for the four-times world champions.
</P>
<P>
Brazil went into the match under tremendous pressure for
gaining only eight points from five games, yet got the perfect
start with a sixth minute goal by Alex.
</P>
<P>
Argentina took 20 minutes to find their rhythm, with Ariel
Ortega giving the Brazil defense plenty of problems.
</P>
<P>
But Brazil increased the lead in first half injury time when
Vampeta scored an excellent goal.
</P>
<P>
Brazil were still celebrating when Argentina pulled a goal back.
Substitute Almeida, who had replaced the injured Javier Zanetti,
scored with a powerful left-foot drive.
</P>
<P>
Six minutes into the second half, Vampeta scored his second
goal in the match, helping Brazil regain its two-goal advantage.
</P>
<P>
Argentina remained top of the South American qualifying group
with 15 points from six games while Brazil moved into second place
with 11, ahead of Uruguay on goals scored. 
</P>
</TEXT>
