<HEADLINE> Venus, Seles Reach Quarter-finals at Bank of the West Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon champion Venus
Williams and two-times champion Monica Seles both advanced to the
quarter-finals on Wednesday at the WTA Bank of the West Classic in
Stanford, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Williams of America ousted Russia's Tatiana
Panova 6-2, 6-2, while American Seles, third seed, beat her
compatriot Meghann Shaughnessy 7-5, 6-3, at the first US hardcourt
tuneup for the US Open.
</P>
<P>
Williams was runner-ups of the event in the past two years,
losing twice to world number two Lindsay Davenport, who begins her
bid for a third consecutive title Thursday against Australia's
Nicole Pratt.
</P>
<P>
But Williams defeated Davenport in the Wimbledon final after
ousting world number one Martina Hingis in the quarter-finals and
sister Serena Williams in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Seles, the 19990 and 1992 champion of the event, was sidelined
with a broken foot at the start of the year but has won three
titles and compiled a 34-6 record this season. 
</P>
