<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Wells Discovered in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Archeologists have discovered some
rare wells dating back to 2,000 years ago in this northern port
city.
</P>
<P>
They reported that there are seven wells belonging to the
Warring States period (475-221 BC) and 11 to the Han Dynasty (202
BC- 260 AD). Most of them are shallow, only one to two meters deep.
</P>
<P>
The finding shows that ancient people used soil, bricks and
wood to construct the wells.
</P>
<P>
The archeologists have also discovered several pottery pots for
fetching water and some spindles, shovels and grindstones.
</P>
<P>
The most rare relic is a wooden slip on which some Taoist words
were inscribed.
</P>
<P>
The wells were found in a village in Ji county in the suburbs
of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The finding is expected to provide clues to the study of
ancient people's living conditions around Tianjin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000727.0264 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Development Zone to Become Cyber-culture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin Economic and Technological
Development Zone, the most rapidly growing development zone in
China, has initiated a digitalization project recently.
</P>
<P>
The project is in essence a "e-community" established to be
home to several thousand of businesses in the Development Zone
aiming at supporting e-business by building an information
platform.
</P>
<P>
The cyber-project also offers on-line education and all other
information services in addition to e-commerce.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics showed that the Tianjin Development Zone has
been leading all the other development zones in China by
accomplishing 11.96 billion yuan (over 1.4 billion U.S. dollars)
of GDP during the first half of this year, an increase of 21
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Sino-foreign joint ventures, cooperative businesses and
exclusively foreign-owned enterprises in the development zone
reported 2.85 billion yuan of profits during the first five months
of this year, an increase of 15 percent over the same period last
year. And all indicators in the economic performances of these
enterprises during the period were the best in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Motorola and Samsung contributed more than half of the total
output value of the development zone during the January-May period.
</P>
<P>
The development zone has also approved 63 foreign investment
projects involving 503.6 million U.S. dollars of overseas capital
in the January-June period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
