<HEADLINE> Indian Poacher Shot Dead in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- One Indian poacher was shot dead
while three others were injured by Nepali forest guards Wednesday
in Nepal's Shukla Phanta Wildlife Reserve that borders India, The
Kathmandu Post said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The reserve's chief warden Yuba Raj Regmi was quoted as saying
that the poachers were spotted by the Royal Nepali Army personnel
posted for the security of the reserve near the Indo-Nepal border
area.
</P>
<P>
One poacher was killed and three injured after the security
staff opened fire at them, Regmi said, adding that it was the
poachers who first opened fire at the army personnel.
</P>
<P>
The poachers had killed a deer in the reserve, he said.
</P>
<P>
A team of Nepali officials have left for the site for detailed
investigations, said Regmi. 
