<DOCNO> XIE20000727.0274 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korean Semiconductor Export Surges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 27 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's export of
semiconductors amounted to 11.9 billion U.S. dollars in the first
half of this year, up 31.8 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The country's chip exports rose 63.2 percent last month from
the same month last year to 2.39 billion dollars, the second
highest monthly figure in history. The last highest monthly
figure was registered in November 1995 with 2.43 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Memory chips for personal computers worth 5.73 billion dollars
were exported in the first half of this year, up 54.8 percent from
the previous year while non-memory chips export registered 5.57
billion dollars, up 13.9 percent. Semiconductor devices export
rose 33.3 percent to 540 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the outstanding performance, the Commerce, Industry
and Energy Ministry Thursday revised this year's semiconductor
export target to 22.5 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Analysts forecast market demand in the third quarter of this
year will surpass the supply of DRAM chips, which take more than
half of the total export items, and the demand for DRAM is
expected to increase even more substantially in coming years.
</P>
</TEXT>
