<HEADLINE> Barcelona Ready to Sell Six Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Barcelona's new coach Llorenc Serra
Ferrer has decided to sell six international players who are
surplus to the club's requirements, according to reports by
Spanish state television on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Spanish state television said on Wednesday, Serra Ferrer has
told goalkeepers Vitor Baia and Ruud Hesp, defenders Frederic Dehu,
Winston Bogarde and Samuel Okunowo and midfielder Jari Litmanen
they can all start looking for new clubs for the new season.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese international Baia is the big surprise on the list.
He has just returned from a loan spell at Porto and was widely
expected to be staying on after the departure of Van Gaal.
</P>
<P>
Okunowo also spent last season on loan at Benfica and the
Nigerian defender was not expected to be invited back into the
first team.
</P>
<P>
Dutch international goalkeeper Hesp has been at the Nou Camp
for the last three seasons but lost his place last term after a
poor spell.
</P>
<P>
Dutch international defender Winston Bogarde may head for
England's premier league.
</P>
<P>
Finnish midfielder Litmanen and French centre-back Dehu both
arrived on free transfers last summer but failed to win a post in
the starting lineup as they struggled for form and fitness.
</P>
<P>
Dutch winger Boudewijn Zenden, who had an excellent performance
at Euro 2000, is also expected to leave the club, with Lazio
reported to be ready to pay 2,150 million pesetas ($12.15 million).
</P>
