<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tennis Indoor Stadium Not Appropriate for ABC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Badminton Association of
Indonesia (PBSI) secretary-general Leo Chandra Wiranata considers
the Senayan Tennis Indoor Stadium here inappropriate to host the
JVC Asian Badminton Championships (ABC) in November.
</P>
<P>
"You saw how crowded the venue was during the final (of the
recent Indonesia Open), especially during the men's singles when
Taufik Hidayat faced Ong Ewe Hock of Malaysia. Can you imagine
what would have happened if Taufik lost?" Wiranata was quoted as
saying by the Jakarta Post Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The spectators were too close to the courts and it could have
endangered the safety of the players," he added.
</P>
<P>
About 4,500 people thronged the stadium on Sunday, exceeding
the maximum capacity of 4,000.
</P>
<P>
Ong complained that some spectators threw mineral water bottles
at him when he defeated local opponent Johan Hadikusuma in the
semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Wiranata said the most appropriate venue was either the Senayan
Indoor Stadium or the Jakarta Convention Center.
</P>
<P>
"We can set up the stadium as we did for the Thomas Cup final
championships in 1990 but it will cost a lot, especially nowadays
with sponsors being hard to get. The most ideal place is the
convention center which has an underground tunnel to the nearby
Hilton Hotel. But definitely, it will cost a fortune as the rent
fee is much higher than the stadium," he said.
</P>
<P>
The ABC's venue was decided in the Asian Badminton
Confederation executive council meeting.
</P>
<P>
Wiranata said if the event was staged outside Jakarta, only
three cities -- Surabaya, Semarang and Surakarta -- had the
facilities to do so.
</P>
<P>
He said PBSI and IMG, who hold the event rights, must consider
Indonesia's reputation as host.
</P>
<P>
"We should take care in our image, especially if Chinese
players are competing in the event," he said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia will not only stage the championships but also host
the annual general meeting and the referees certification.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
