<HEADLINE> New Attraction Planned for South China's Sanya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A new man-made isle and a new
passenger berth will be built in offshore areas near Sanya, a
popular tourist destination on the southern tip of Hainan
Province.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the projected isle and berth will
be constructed by Zhongcheng International Passenger Transport and
Tourism Development Co. Ltd of Sanya, with designs provided by the
No.4 Navigational Projects Survey and Design Institute of the
Chinese Ministry of Communications.
</P>
<P>
The man-made isle will cover an area of 33.3 hectares and the
new berth will have a dead weight tonnage (DWT) of 40,000. The two
projects, planned to cost about 80 million yuan, will take two
years to finish.
</P>
<P>
The new tourist attractions are designed to stand strong storms
and tidal waves and to host 600,000 passengers annually. 
