<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wild Takins Spotted in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese zoologists have found a
group of 20 wild takins in a forest region in Zhen'an county,
Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The sighting of the rare beasts, which are under State
protection, is believed to be the first in almost 40 years, local
experts said.
</P>
<P>
There were many reports of traces of wild takins in the region
before the 1960s, but the animals seemed to have disappeared in
the area as a result of the exceeding logging in 1970s and 1980s.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the forest area is increasing thanks to the
ban on logging and efficient afforestation drive in the region.
</P>
<P>
The sighting on the wild takins indicates that the ecological
environment has been greatly improved, the experts said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
