<HEADLINE> Patient Swallowed Watch Saved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A 77-year-old man who gulped a
watch by mistake has been saved in Shanghai, according to Tuesday'
s Wenhui Daily.
</P>
<P>
The renowned Jinshan Hospital in Shanghai treated this
schizophrenic man from Haiyan, a city of east China's Zhejiang
Province, who gulped a stainless watch last Monday.
</P>
<P>
The choked patient was soon rushed to the Jinshan Hospital
after the local hospital failed in taking out the watch.
</P>
<P>
The watch was hard to bring out because of its big size, slick
surface and difficulty to locate. Patient's hypertension and
chronic bronchitis also add difficulties to the treatment and the
senior man was in great danger.
</P>
<P>
However, Chief doctor Xu Lingen and his aides finally succeeded
in taking out the watch with the guidance of laryngoscope. The
patient left the hospital the next day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
