<HEADLINE> South China City Strives to Attract Talent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- One hundred and twenty-three
students doing doctorate or master's degrees across China began
their one-month research tour of Guangzhou, capital of Guangdong
Province, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During the one-month research tour, the students are expected
to do research on special topics to gain some knowledge about the
environment and start up businesses in this southern Chinese
economic center.
</P>
<P>
The move was initiated by the organizational department of
Guangzhou City Commission of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
the personnel bureau of Guangzhou City and Guangzhou City
Committee of the Communist Youth League (CYL) in cooperation with
CYL organizations in key state universities across the country. It
is designed to publicize Guangzhou's policies on personnel, and
attract more talented people.
</P>
<P>
The students have received professional training in areas
ranging from computing, electronics, machinery, material science,
to biochemistry, construction, environment and law.
</P>
<P>
"They are the right kind of qualified personnel Guangzhou
desperately wants to have for its future development," said a
local official.
</P>
<P>
The students were warmly welcomed by local organizations. Li
Shanpei, deputy Party secretary of Guangzhou presented each
student with a golden key, saying Guangzhou would always extending
open arms to these students. 
</P>
