<HEADLINE> East China Province Reports High Export Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Exports of east China's Fujian
Province topped 6.09 billion U.S. dollars during the first half of
the year, a year-on-year increase of 30.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial government said that state-
owned enterprises, overseas-funded businesses and private firms
have all contributed to the growth.
</P>
<P>
Exports from Fujian's private firms surged 281 percent to reach
142 million U.S. dollars during the January-June period.
</P>
<P>
Major export commodities include roast eel, displays, stone
works, and shoes.
</P>
<P>
Nationwide, China's export volume rose 38.3 percent to hit 114.
5 billion U.S.dollars in the first half of the year.  
</P>
