<DOCNO> XIE20000727.0313 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Welfare Fund Helps Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The China Welfare Fund for the
Handicapped (CWFH) spent 9.7 million yuan (1.17 million U.S.
dollars) last year to help 60 million disabled people with their
recovery, education, and even providing financial aid.
</P>
<P>
Trustees of CWFH said that the fund collected a total of 14.47
million yuan from home and abroad last year, according to today's
China Daily.
</P>
<P>
"The fund will not only continue to care for the life,
employment, recovery and education of the disabled this year, but
will also focus on improving the job opportunities for handicapped
people in western China," said Deng Pufang, head of the fund.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the fund also plans to organize some large-scale
activities with the aim to encourage disabled people. And it will
spend nearly 20 million yuan this year helping the handicapped.
</P>
<P>
About 73 percent of handicapped children are enrolled in the
State's nine-year compulsory education program and almost 1,400
disabled students entered universities and colleges last year,
CWFH sources said.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 16 million disabled people found jobs last year with the
help of the fund. Another 2.39 million poverty-stricken
handicapped were helped and 1.6 million received financial aid.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
