<HEADLINE> Police Called on to Keep Order in Poor Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Public Security
has ordered local police to see to it that social order is
maintained so that the government's strategy to develop the
economically-backward western region will go smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The ministry recently issued a circular urging local public
security departments to come up with ways to meet the new policing
demands that will most likely arise, especially transnational
crime and misuse of funds.
</P>
<P>
It also asks all police departments to concentrate on combating
pornography, drug-related crimes, gambling, and activities
detrimental to the local infrastructure and environment.
</P>
<P>
The residential registration system in these areas should be
reformed comprehensively, which will help attract people to work
in the underdeveloped areas, it says.
</P>
<P>
The circular also urges to enhance the management of customs
entry and exit to better facilitate overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
The traffic administration and fire control departments should
also play their part in ensuring safety of the local people, the
circular says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
