<HEADLINE> Weah Cancels Contract with AC Milan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 26 (Xinhua) -- AC Milan have agreed to cancel the
contract of Liberian striker George Weah allowing him to leave the
club on a free transfer.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Milan said the player and the club talked over
the issue and made the decision mutually on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Weah had one year remaining on his contract but the decision
will not come as a huge shock to Milan supporters.
</P>
<P>
After a disagreement with Milan coach Alberto Zaccheroni last
season, Weah was loaned to English premier league club Chelsea but
he was not offered a permanent deal by the London team.
</P>
<P>
Weah joined Milan from Paris Saint Germain in 1995 and helped
them to Serie A titles in 1996 and 1999. In 1995 he became the
first African to be voted European Player of the Year.
</P>
<P>
The 33-year-old Liberian international made 114 Serie A
appearances for Milan. 
</P>
