<HEADLINE> Chinese Men's Volleyball Team Fail to Qualify for Sydney Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese men's national
volleyball team Wednesday night failed to qualify for the 2000
Sydney Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
On the third and final day of the Olympic qualifying men's
volleyball tournament held at Greece's Peace and Friendship
Stadium in Piraeus, spain easily qualified for the Sydney Olmpics
by defeating Greece 3-0 ( 27-25, 25-17, 25-20).
</P>
<P>
Spain ranked first with six points at the tournament by winning
all its three matches with China, Greece and Tunisia respectively
while China gained five points Wednesday after beating tunisia 3-2
(25-21, 25-21, 23-25, 25-27, 15-12). China also defeated Greece 3-
0 on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Greece, the host country, got four points and Tunisia abtained
three points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
