<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chavez Expects Golden Age for Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Coming July 30 elections will be
the most important in Venezuela's history, because from them the
first president of the fifth Bolivian Republic will come and will
lead Venezuela on a totally new path.
</P>
<P>
Under the motto of "give Venezuela hard push" at midnight
Thursday, the election campaign will come to an end. It is the
third election in little over a year.
</P>
<P>
According to the new Constitution of the Republic approved in
December 1999, the President may be reelected for another 6 year
period.
</P>
<P>
Among the 3 candidates, President Hugo Chavez heads election
preferences, with support from 5th Republican Movement, the
governing party.
</P>
<P>
In order to fulfill election promises, following his triumph in
December 1998 elections with 56.2 of votes, Chavez placed emphasis
on political reform during the 15 months of his term and decreed a
new Magna Charta.
</P>
<P>
In his governmental plan, the President and Presidential
Candidate assured that if he's elected he'll head again Venezuela'
s economic reactivation, as plenty has been done in the political
field, and it's time to hold the rudder in the economic one.
</P>
<P>
In economy, the President will look to stimulate the formation
of national private capital, absorbing more foreign investment.
He considers that outside capital will have a complementary role
to that of the State.
</P>
<P>
President Chavez plans to give priority to private national
fields, specifically that of petroleum and will orient outside
capital toward natural gas, petrochemistry, orimulsion and coal.
</P>
<P>
 Orimulsion, a coal substitute fuel, is a mixture of water and
heavy based crude product found in the Orinoco River of Venezuel
</P>
<P>
Chavez said that Venezuela will strengthen the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) in defense of crude's prices.
In Venezuela, Chavez' government will diversify exports and
develop clear anti-inflation and anti-devaluation policies.
</P>
<P>
Chavez cast the idea, an immense desire, to "leave the age of
steel in order to  march Venezuela into the golden age".
</P>
<P>
In social issues, Chavez promised to generate employment,
eradicate poverty, achieve social justice, improve the quality of
life and security's situation.
</P>
<P>
Although up to now nobody casts doubt on Chavez' success, many
consider this will be hard with the participation of his main
rival and ex-colleage of frustrated 1992 coup d'etat, former
Zulia state governor, Francisco Arias Cardenas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000727.0328 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Donates 20,000 U.S. Dollars to Greek Red Cross </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China Thursday donated 20,000 U.S.
dollars to the Hellenic Red Cross in a bid to help relieve the
people in Greece's forest fires-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
During a presenting ceremony here Thursday, Chinese Ambassador
to Greece Zhen Jianguo, on behalf of the Chinese Red Cross, handed
over a check of 20,000 dollars to Elli Dimitriou, Secretary
General of the Hellenic Red Cross.
</P>
<P>
He said that the donation was the symbol of friendship between
the peoples of the two countries that enjoy long ancient
civilization in the world.
</P>
<P>
On her part, Dimitriou thanked the Chinese Red Cross for the
donation, saying that the Greek people would never forget this.
</P>
<P>
Currently, some 70,000 hectares of forests have been destroyed
and a lot of houses burnt in a spate of forest fires across Greece
since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Chinese Red Cross also donated a sum of 30,000
U.S. dollars to his Greek counterpart following a powerful
earthquake that rocked Athens in September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
