<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five Mexicans Die due to Toxic Gases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 27 (Xinhua) -- About 5 people died Thursday
due to gases sent out by a black water pit in a processing
warehouse in Mexico's northeastern Nayarit state.
</P>
<P>
Director of Municipal Public Security Xocoyotzin Vega said the
incident happened at a fish and seafood warehouse in Santiago
Ixcuintla.
</P>
<P>
Vega said that worker Eusebio Sanchez Alvarez was getting ready
to clean the pit, when the handle of the hose he carried fell off
and when he tried to retrieve it, the gases made effect, whereby
he grew weak and fell into the smelly waters.
</P>
<P>
Four of this mates when realizing what had occurred, tried to
help him, but the same thing happened to them, falling into the
contaminated water pit, said Vega.
</P>
<P>
Minutes later, personnel from Security Headquarters came to
rescue the workers, but they'd already passed away. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
