<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
Thursday closed lower with the benchmark IPC index falling by 140.
99 points, or 2.09 percent, to 6,607.49 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 56.184 million shares worth some 112.052
million U.S. dollars against Wednesday's 49.978 million shares
worth some 101.405 million dollars .
</P>
<P>
The Mexican peso stood at 9.362 for one U.S. dollar for sale
and 9.360 for purchase, compared with Wednesday's 9.365 for sale
and 9.358 for purchase, for the Bank of Mexico, the country's
central bank. 
</P>
