<HEADLINE> Clinton Meets with Philippine President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 27 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton on
Thursday met with visiting Philippine President Joseph Estrada at
the White House to discuss how to strengthen bilateral government
and business ties.
</P>
<P>
Topics of the meeting included regional security, cleanup of
toxic waste from former U.S. military bases, compensation for
Filipino World War II veterans who fought for the U.S. military
and economic issues.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, Estrada, who arrived here Wednesday, was
greeted with a honor guard at the White House gate.
</P>
<P>
Estrada is accompanied on his visit by several members of his
cabinet and about 100 Philippine business leaders. After
Washington, he is expected to visit New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
