<HEADLINE> London And Frankfurt Hit By Nokia Gloom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 27 (Xinhua) - London and Frankfurt extended their
losses Thursday as a 15 percent slide in Finish mobile phone giant
Nokia and a weaker showing on Nasdaq.
</P>
<P>
Dealers in London were left confused after a rollercoaster
session left shares closing on their lows despite a wave of
generally bullish company news.
</P>
<P>
With the results season in full swing, a welter of blue chip
company announcements sent the FTSE-100 Index up almost 70 points
in early trading.
</P>
<P>
But by the close the benchmark index had succumbed to selling
pressure and ended the session down 35 points, or 0.55 percent at
6352.1.
</P>
<P>
Cable company Telewest Communications was down 7.3 percent and
mobile phone service provider Vodafone AirTouch off 4.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Financial shares were weaker for a second straight day,with
mortgage bank Halifax down 4.7 percent even though six-month
profit rose 21 percent.
</P>
<P>
The pan-European FTSE Eurotop 300 was down 1.1 percent to 1609.
06, with its electronics equipment component down 3.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Frankfurt's Xetra Dax index fell 118.68 points to 7183.44
pulled lower by a 10-percent decline for electronic components
maker Epcos.
</P>
<P>
The CAC 40 blue chip index closed up 18.53 points, or 0.3
percent, to 6511.53, with Alcatel gaining 3.9 percent and bucking
the negative trend among rivals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
