<HEADLINE> Millennium Dome to Become Theme Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A Japanese-financed company has won
the battle to take over the troubled 758 million pound (1.15
billion U.S. dollars) Millennium Dome from the beginning of next
year, the British government announced on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dome Europe will turn the South London attraction into an
amusement park. The firm edged out a rival, more business-
orientated, bid from the Legacy consortium.
</P>
<P>
Supported by Japanese finance house Nomura, Dome Europe plans
to pump around 800 million pounds (1.28 billion dollars) into the
Dome and its surrounding area. Within three years, the company
hopes to be attracting five million visitors a year to the Dome.
</P>
<P>
Dome Europe has won the contract to take over the Millennium
Dome, Cabinet Office minister Lord Falconer said.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to turn the Dome into a hi-tech leisure
attraction based on the theme of Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
