<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombian FM to Visit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Colombian minister will meet coming July 30 in China's
capital his Mexican counterpart, in order to carry out together
this Rio Group troika visit, due to 10th anniversary of the
dialog system between the largest Latin American and Chinese
political concertation group.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan will also meet his
counterparts from Mexico, Colombia and Chile to evaluate advances
obtained in the last 10 years in rapprochement and mutual support
between the parties and analyze how to tighten even further future
links.
</P>
<P>
Besides, according to the same source, the heads of Chinese and
Colombian diplomacy will cover matters regarding bilateral
relations, the Andean Community and Colombia's security system,
among others.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit to China of the troika group, made up
by Colombia, Mexico and Chile. Rio Group was created in December
1986 in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, formed by Contadora Group and
Lima Group.
</P>
<P>
In year 2000, Colombia assumes the rotating Secretariat of Rio
Group.
</P>
</TEXT>
