<HEADLINE> Mexican President-elect to Visit US, Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President-elect Vicent
Fox is planning to visit Canada on August 22 and United States on
August 24.
</P>
<P>
Fox's governmental transition team reported Thursday by
communique these visits will be done in order to correspond to
greetings and congratulations both leaders sent him when he won
July 2 elections.
</P>
<P>
Fox's first visit will be to Ottawa, Canada, at Canada's Prime
Minister's official residence and the second on August 24 at
White House Oval Office with Clinton.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in United States, Fox will meet U.S.
presidential candidates, Democrat Albert Gore, and Republican
George W. Bush, who will compete in the next elections.
</P>
<P>
Previous to this journey to North America's countries, Fox will
make another journey from August 7-10 to Brazil, Chile and
Argentina. 
</P>
</TEXT>
